    <hr class="my-4" id="hrinstall">
    <div class="row">
        <p class="pinstall">
            The module is a good support for admin client, because it gives the admin the possibility to see how the clients engaged in the
            game are connected. The module can be intialized in just 3 steps</p>
    </div>
    <div class="text-center">
        <img src="/style/img/graphh.jpg" class="rounded" alt="graph">
    </div>
    <h4 class="pinstall">Setup</h4>
    <ol class="ollatency">
        <li>The first step is installing the via.js module in the terminal</li>
        <div class="installcomands"><p> npm install vis</p></div>

        <li>Now, you need to import the module in server.js and to move network out of createServer in order to declare it
         as a local variable. Then, you need to add the server commands to the Network Module.</li>
    <div class="installcomands"><p> import {NetworkModule} from './src/modules/NetworkModule'</p>
    <p> let network = Network.pairs(8)</p>
        <p> NetworkModule.addServerCommands(commands, network)</p>
    </div>
    <li>On the last step, you need to add the import module in admin-client.js file. The module is declared between events and before the
        server is created. Add the setupClient after the admin-client is created.
    </li>
    <div class="installcomands"><p> import {NetworkModule} from './src/modules/NetworkModule'</p>
                                <p> NetworkModule.addAdminClientEvents(events)</p>
                                <p> NetworkModule.setupClient(admin)</p>
    </div>
    </ol>
    <h4 class="pinstall">Overview</h4>
    <p class="pinstall">
        In order to get a better understanding of how Network Module works, we suggest you to see the source code by clicking
       on the <a href="https://github.com/asbjoern1982/monsterr-modules/blob/master/src/modules/LatencyModule.js">Github link</a>.
    </p>

